  <arm_group>
    <arm_group_label>One-lung ventilation</arm_group_label>
    <arm_group_type>Experimental</arm_group_type>
    <description>Before surgical incision, 2-min of OLV followed by 2-min of TLV (1 cycle) is performed for 5 cycles.</description>
  </arm_group>
  <arm_group>
    <arm_group_label>Two-lung ventilation</arm_group_label>
    <arm_group_type>No Intervention</arm_group_type>
    <description>Maintain two-lung ventilation until surgical incision</description>
  </arm_group>
  <intervention>
    <intervention_type>Other</intervention_type>
    <intervention_name>One-lung ventilation</intervention_name>
    <description>The patient undergoing thoracic surgery is intubated with double lumen tube after induction of general anesthesia with propofol and remifentanil.
In the intervention group, 5 cycles of one-lung ventilation preconditioning (2-min of one-lung ventilation and 2-min of two-lung ventilation for 1 cycle) is performed before surgical incision. One-lung ventilation is done at dependent lung with FiO2 100% and tidal volume 6 ml kg-1. Two-lung ventilation is done with FiO2 50%, tidal volume 8 ml kg-1.</description>
    <arm_group_label>One-lung ventilation</arm_group_label>
    <other_name>Preconditioning</other_name>
  </intervention>
